# NickelCoverFix

Keeps your book covers showing even when Kobo can't fetch them — **offline**, or after a sync changes the
cover id so Kobo would otherwise draw the title/author **placeholder**. It mirrors the cover **Kobo itself
already had**, keyed by the book's stable ContentID, and shows that instead.

**No DRM, no decryption, no book files.** It only ever copies a cover Kobo already obtained legitimately.
Kobo's own cache (`.kobo-images`) is never written. Remove the mod (or this folder) to fully revert.

## How it works
- **Capture** — as each of *your* books is shown, its cover is mirrored to
  `.adds/nickel-cover-fix/covers/`: a fast raw copy from Kobo's on-disk cache when available, or the
  rendered image for covers that were only in memory. Store/recommendation covers are never touched.
- **Serve** — when a cover would be a placeholder, the mirrored cover is shown instead (scaled to size:
  a smaller copy for the library, a full-res copy for the lock screen). This covers the library grid, the
  lock/sleep screen, and the home screen's **"Now Reading"** shelf.
- **Repair Book Covers** (More menu) — mirror your whole library at once, with a progress bar.

Because the mirror is keyed by the stable ContentID, it survives offline gaps and cover-id changes.

## It's active on install
No arming needed. To disable, set `ncf_enabled:0` in `config` (over USB) and reboot. To remove it, delete
the `uninstall` file in this folder and reboot.

## Cover mode (`ncf_force_serve`)
- `1` (default) — **scoped override**: your library books show our own copy (offline-consistent); store,
  recommendations, previews and new/cloud books fall through to Kobo untouched.
- `0` — **graceful fallback**: Kobo's real cover when available, our copy only to rescue a placeholder.

## If a book still shows a placeholder
That means its cover has never been available for us to copy (never on disk, never rendered). Go online and
run **Settings > Device information > "Repair your Kobo account"** to fetch covers, then tap **Repair Book
Covers**.

## Config (`config`, seeded from `default`)
- `ncf_enabled` — master kill-switch.
- `ncf_capture` — mirror covers as books are shown (else only Repair populates).
- `ncf_serve` — show a mirrored cover instead of the placeholder.
- `ncf_force_serve` — cover mode (see above).
- `ncf_menu` — add the Repair Book Covers row to the More page.
- `ncf_log` — write `nickelcoverfix.log`.
- `ncf_debug_dot` — stamp served covers with a bullseye (debugging).

## Uninstall
Delete the `uninstall` file in this folder and reboot (removes the mod and the mirror folder; `.kobo-images`
is untouched).
